People with symptoms should stay isolated for a minimum of 10 days after the first day they developed symptoms, plus another 3 days after the end of symptoms – when they are without fever and without respiratory symptoms.  People without symptoms should stay isolated for a minimum of 10 days after testing positive. Monitor the symptoms of the person with COVID-19 infection’s symptoms regularly, and call your healthcare provider immediately if you see any of these danger signs:Difficulty breathingChest painConfusionLoss of speech or mobilityFor young children, seek immediate medical care if you notice any of these symptoms:High feverRapid breathingLethargy or not interacting when awakeDifficulty in feeding (unable to drink or breastfeed)Blue lips or face
